{
  "stem": "1061.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had-- they gave us what was called coffee, which was water-- which was nothing-- with a little piece of bread that was for the day.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was to last you the day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had to line up, to leave through the gate that says, [SPEAKING GERMAN], you know, 'Work makes you free.' Cut marsh in the marshes.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We would walk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We would-- I don't really know how far, but it had to be a distance, a few miles.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were these private homes along the way, and people were living lives in those homes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were geranium boxes in the window.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There with pillows being aired.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Who these people were who lived there, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Could be the attendant, the Auschwitz attendant, the German attendants with their families or could be-- I don't know who.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But those were homes as we knew homes to be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were so far away from anything that could even be called human.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, that-- you think in pictures.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That picture of walking by the homes with the pillows in the windows and the geraniums and such, going to the marshes, standing there in water cutting the-- in the marshes, then coming back to be beaten and line up again.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if anybody didn't line up, you-- they could keep you there forever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then going to sleep inside the barracks, nine people to a-- you know, they had bunks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One bunk had nine women.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we would sleep head to foot because nine the same way, the same direction, would not fit.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So you had to-- to sleep one way, one this way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the humiliations-- the daily humiliations of the people who were running the barracks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
